volumeInfo.description: Do you suffer with anticipation? Wake up tired? Do not tolerate working with slow people? Have headaches or muscle? You forget things easily? If you answered "yes" to any of these questions, it is likely to suffer the Accelerated Thought Syndrome (ATS). Considered by Augusto Cury shrink as the new evil of the century, supplanting the depression, it affects much of the world's population. In this book, you will understand how the human mind works to be able to slow down their thinking, manage their emotions effectively and redeem their quality of life.

searchInfo.textSnippet: Considerada pelo psiquiatra Augusto Cury como o novo mal do século, suplantando a depressão, ela acomete grande parte da população mundial.
